- "rich variety of tags" refers to a high number of tags;
- "stands tall" and "shining above all others" refer to the game with the highest number of awards, and in case of a tie, the highest number of tags;
- "vast garden of gaming" refers to the collection of games in the database.

- 'free-to-play' refers to games that are available to play without any initial cost;
- 'awards' refer to accolades or recognitions received by the game;
- 'platforms' refer to the different systems or devices on which the game can be played.

- "Decorated" refers to the number of awards a game has received;
- "Versatile" refers to the number of platforms and tags associated with a game;
- The total count is the sum of platform_count, award_count, and tag_count for each game.

sql:
SELECT AVG(award_count) AS average_award_count
FROM (
    SELECT game_id, COUNT(game_award_id) AS award_count
    FROM game_awards
    GROUP BY game_id
) AS game_awards_count;

